abstract: Hillary Clinton beats Bernie Sanders in Nevada Democratic primary, rebounding after New Hampshire defeat and reassuring supporters of her ability to draw broad support; Clinton's win rests on backing of minority voters and casino workers in state where populist anger made her victory less than certain.
lead_paragraph: Early organizing in the state and a last-minute push for support from casino workers, many of them black or Hispanic, were credited in Mrs. Clinton’s victory.

byline.original: By AMY CHOZICK and PATRICK HEALY
byline.contributor: Amy Chozick reported from Las Vegas, and Patrick Healy from New York.

headline.main: Hillary Clinton Beats Bernie Sanders in Nevada Caucuses
headline.print_headline: Trump and Clinton Are Victorious; Bush Drops Out as Field Narrows
